A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 20, 2025, as Buc-ee's Day at the Georgia State Capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, founded in 1982 in Clute, Texas, Buc-ee's has become a nationally recognized
4 travel center brand known for its unparalleled customer service, pristine facilities, and
5 commitment to community investment; and
6 WHEREAS, Buc-ee's has successfully expanded into multiple states, including Georgia, with
7 established locations in Warner Robins and Calhoun and upcoming travel centers in Monroe
8 County and Brunswick, strengthening its presence and economic impact in the state; and
9 WHEREAS, Buc-ee's has announced plans to open a new 74,000-square-foot travel center
10 in Monroe County, Georgia, on a 30-acre site off Interstate 75 at Rumble Road, featuring 120
11 fuel pumps and bringing approximately 200 full-time jobs with competitive wages and
12 benefits to the local economy; and
13 WHEREAS, the Buc-ee's Monroe County location is projected to generate approximately
14 $4 million annually in local tax revenue, supporting economic development and essential
15 public services in the region; and
