16 WHEREAS, Buc-ee's has committed $10 million toward significant infrastructure
17 improvements in Monroe County, including widening Rumble Road, enhancing the I-75
18 interchange, installing traffic signals, and constructing a roundabout at the store entrance,
19 demonstrating its dedication to responsible development and community partnership; and
20 WHEREAS, Buc-ee's investment in Georgia contributes to increased tourism, job creation,
21 and business growth, benefiting local communities and reinforcing Georgia's reputation as
22 a prime location for business expansion; and
23 WHEREAS, Buc-ee's embodies the entrepreneurial spirit and economic vitality that make
24 Georgia a leader in business and commerce, aligning with the state's commitment to fostering
25 growth and innovation.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 recognize March 20, 2025, as Buc-ee's Day at the Georgia State Capitol and commend
28 Buc-ee's for its continued investment in Georgia and its role in enhancing economic
29 development and tourism.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Buc-ee's.
